def load_mnist(path, kind='train'):
    """Load MNIST data from `path`"""
    labels_path = os.path.join(path,
                               '%s-labels-idx1-ubyte.gz'
                               % kind)
    images_path = os.path.join(path,
                               '%s-images-idx3-ubyte.gz'
                               % kind)

    with gzip.open(labels_path, 'rb') as lbpath:
        labels = np.frombuffer(lbpath.read(), dtype=np.uint8,
                               offset=8)

    with gzip.open(images_path, 'rb') as imgpath:
        images = np.frombuffer(imgpath.read(), dtype=np.uint8,
                               offset=16).reshape(len(labels), 784)

    return images, labels

# 
epochs = []
train_losses = []
train_accs = []
valid_losses = []
valid_accs = []

# epochtrain_losstrain_accvalid_lossvalid_acc
pattern = re.compile(r'Epoch (\d+) \|.*learning rate: (\S+)\s+\| Train Loss: (\S+) \| Train Acc: (\S+) \|.*Valid Loss: (\S+) \| Valid Acc: (\S+)')

# 
with open('.\\logs\\train_log.txt', 'r') as file:
    for line in file:
        match = pattern.search(line)
        if match:
            epoch = int(match.group(1))
            epochs.append(epoch)
            
            train_loss = float(match.group(3))
            train_losses.append(train_loss)
            
            train_acc = float(match.group(4))
            train_accs.append(train_acc)
            
            valid_loss = float(match.group(5)) if match.group(5) else None
            valid_losses.append(valid_loss)
            
            valid_acc = float(match.group(6)) if match.group(6) else None
            valid_accs.append(valid_acc)

# 
plt.figure(figsize=(14, 7))

# 
plt.subplot(1, 2, 1)
plt.plot(epochs, train_losses, label='Train Loss', color='blue')
plt.xlabel('Epoch')
plt.ylabel('Loss')
plt.title('Training Loss')
plt.legend()

# 
plt.subplot(1, 2, 2)
plt.plot(epochs, train_accs, label='Train Accuracy', color='orange')
plt.xlabel('Epoch')
plt.ylabel('Accuracy')
plt.title('Training Accuracy')
plt.legend()

# 
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

#
plt.figure(figsize=(14, 7))

# 
plt.subplot(1, 2, 1)
plt.plot(epochs, valid_losses, label='Valid Loss', linestyle='--', color='green')
plt.xlabel('Epoch')
plt.ylabel('Loss')
plt.title('Validation Loss')
plt.legend()

# 
plt.subplot(1, 2, 2)
plt.plot(epochs, valid_accs, label='Valid Accuracy', linestyle='--', color='red')
plt.xlabel('Epoch')
plt.ylabel('Accuracy')
plt.title('Validation Accuracy')
plt.legend()
